Temuka farmer's burn off sparks into dead growth
TESS BRUNTON
Last updated20:46, May 2 2016
After sparking into dead growth, a farmer's burn off was monitored byTemuka fire station volunteerson Milford Clandeboye Rd.Two tankers and a truck arrived at the paddockabout 6.55pm on Monday, but after the situation was accessed,two were sent back to the station.A creek on one side stoppedthe fire from spreading into nearby areas but asprayer tank stayedat the burn off for a couple of hoursin case the conditions changed.
